OpenVPN Cookbook Chapter 2 sample code

The samples in this chapter are all openvpn configuration files, 
some server configuration files and some client configuration files.

Chapter 2 is divided up into 10 recipes. Below is a list of which
configuration file is used in which recipe.

2.1 Setting up the public and private keys
none

2.2 Simple configuration
server: example2-2-server.conf
client: example2-2-client.conf

2.3 Server-side routing
server: basic-udp-server.conf, basic-tcp-server.conf
client: basic-udp-client.conf, basic-tcp-client.conf

2.4 Adding IPv6 support
server: example2-4-server.conf
client: basic-udp-client.conf

2.5 Using 'client-config-dir' files
server: example2-5-server.conf
client: basic-udp-client.conf

2.6 Routing - subnets on both sides
server: example2-6-server.conf
client: basic-udp-client.conf

2.7 Redirecting the default gateway
server: example2-7-server.conf
client: basic-udp-client.conf

2.8 Redirecting the IPv6 default gateway
server: example2-8-server.conf
client: basic-udp-client.conf

2.9 Using an 'ifconfig-pool' block
server: example2-9-server.conf
client1: basic-udp-client.conf
client2: basic-udp-client.ovpn, basic-tcp-client.ovpn

2.10 Using the status file
server: example2-10-server.conf
client1: basic-udp-client.conf
client2: basic-udp-client.ovpn

2.11 Management interface
server: basic-udp-server.conf
client: example2-11.ovpn

2.10 Proxy-arp
server: example2-12-server.conf
client: basic-udp-client.ovpn
scripts: proxyarp-connect.sh, proxyarp-disconnect.sh

